State moves to delete the penalty enhancer on count 1, bail jumping.   Motion granted.   
Count 1 - Bail Jumping - No contest plea.   
Count 2 - Possess THC (2nd + offense) - No contest plea.   Convicted.    
Count 1 - Sentence is withheld.   Defendant is placed on probation to DOC for eighteen (18) months.   Conditions of probation are: 
1) Assessment/treatment/counseling as deemed appropriate by the Department's assessment process; 
2) Maintain absolute sobriety except for prescriptions taken in prescribed doses; 
3) Submit to random urine screens and pay for same; 
4) Maintain full-time employment/schooling combination; 
5) Forty-five (45) days jail imposed and stayed, to be imposed upon the agent's discretion and upon order of the court; 
6) Pay costs of action; 
7) Pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC; 
8) Submit DNA sample.  
